<TITLE> New wage scales for journalists </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 25 (bdnews24.com)  The government has published the gazette of the Seventh Wage Board Award 2008 for journalists, press workers and employees of newspapers and news agencies. In a statement issued Sunday, the Press Information Department said the gazette notification was published on May 22 with the award coming into effect at the same time. The Seventh Newspaper Wage Board submitted its report to chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Earlier on May 7, recommending new scales of wages, allowances and other welfare benefits for the staffers of newspapers and news agencies.
